Here is an example of a basic HTML page using Tailwind CSS for a SaaS landing page:

**index.html**
```html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, a initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SaaS Landing Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tailwindcss@2.2.19/dist/tailwind.min.css">
    <style>
        /* Add some custom styles to make the page look more modern */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, ( sans-serif );
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
        }

       .hero {
            background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3));
            background-size: cover;
            height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
        }

       .pricing-table {
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body class="h-screen bg-gray-100">

    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="container mx-auto p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-12">
            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl xl:text-6xl font-bold mb-4">Welcome to <span class="text-primary-500">SaaS App</span></h1>
